Before taking the AZ-900 exam, review the following areas:

* Cloud concepts
* Azure global infrastructure
* Compute services
* Networking
* Storage services
* Identity and access management
* Security and governance
* Monitoring and management
* Pricing, billing, and support
* Business continuity and disaster recovery

Practical preparation should include creating resource groups, virtual machines, storage accounts, virtual networks, and configuring RBAC, policies, and monitoring tools.

A real-life use case is candidates validating both conceptual knowledge and hands-on Azure Portal experience before certification.

A structured revision checklist improves confidence, identifies weak areas, and increases the likelihood of passing the AZ-900 exam on the first attempt.
